Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["notes", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.690546924699486*^9, 
  3.690546925452395*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6a54542e-86b7-49cc-9af2-\
7a878fc8402d"],

Cell["\<\
The interpretation of event sequences in SpinDynamica currently consists of 2 \
stages: 
EventSpecifications converts the sequence into a standardized list of event \
specifications, checking validity, and standardizing chronology and other \
syntax forms. \
\>", "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.68329033033468*^9, 3.683290392267776*^9}, 
   3.683957680998136*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b0a9a083-7a31-4160-bfde-\
14ef45ccf5ce"],

Cell["\<\
Applying EventList to the result converts the EventSpecifications into an \
EventList object containing a list of Event objects, each of which include:
\t*\tevent timing interval
\t*\tstandardized event time interval 
\t\t\t(taking into account the periodicity, or time-translation invariance of \
the event)
\t*\tpropagator calculation procedure
\t*\tHilbert space compatibility
\t*\tevolution background
\t*\tflag showing whether the evolution background has been incorporated into \
the event

The EventList has its own specifications which depend on the specifications \
of the component events. \
\>", "Text",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.683290404946421*^9, 3.683290625015061*^9}, {
   3.683291376000222*^9, 3.683291469796132*^9}, {3.683368731988813*^9, 
   3.683368742157116*^9}, {3.683369501592431*^9, 3.683369502670076*^9}, {
