   3.46425742625841*^9}, {3.464689352215589*^9, 3.464689353069914*^9}, 
   3.6831109017853646`*^9, 3.683957681047388*^9},
 AspectRatioFixed->
  True,ExpressionUUID->"03f89ecf-f14d-437b-b70c-d97a5299587c"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{"EventSpecifications", "::", "usage"}], "=", 
   "\"\<EventSpecifications[events] converts events into standard form. The \
list of events has the syntax {event1,event2...} where each event may either \
have the form {HamiltonianOperator,duration}  or be a single superoperator, \
for example a RotationSuperoperator or a \
CoherenceOrderFiltrationSuperoperator.  EventSpecifications converts the list \
of events into standard form, including the imposition of right-to-left \
chronology. \nEach event may also carry its internal options. Two examples \
are as follows: \n {opI[\\\"x\\\"],1,Basis\[Rule]ZeemanBasis[]}, and \
{RotationSuperoperator[{\[Pi]/2,\\\"x\\\"},OperatorBasis\[Rule]\
CartesianProductOperatorBasis[]}. These local options are carried into the \
subsequent spin dynamical computations. \nOptions may also be imposed on \
entire blocks of events, using syntax of the form {event1,{event2,event3,c\
\[Rule]d},a\[Rule]b}. In this case the option a\[Rule]b applies to event1, \
while both a\[Rule]b and c\[Rule]d apply to event2 and event3. Such \
constructions may be nested indefinitely. \n.\>\""}], ";"}]], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.683110930825906*^9, 3.683110960429503*^9}, {
  3.683957681054821*^9, 3.683957681056888*^9}, {3.68473148634813*^9, 
  3.684731904786816*^9}, {3.684732038249943*^9, 3.68473207538481*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[2]:=",ExpressionUUID->"6aca0684-d5bc-4463-ad5a-84fe60cce813"]
}, Closed]],

